# Overview
An Alpine container hardened to the CIS benchmark, provided by the [cloud9 team](https://wwwin-github.cisco.com/pages/sto-ccc/cloud9-docs/#/?id=who-we-are).


# Tag Format
* latest: the latest container on the newest Alpine distro version
* x.y : the latest container on the latest Alpine release version, e.g. 3.11
* x.y-1:  the latest container on the previous Alpine release version  e.g. 3.10

NOTE: the latest and previous version tags will update automatically based on current releases of Alpine, and built according to the schedule below.  Older versions may still be available in the repo for up to 30 days.

We build and release these images five times a week, Monday through Friday. Each build will push two tags to the repo. One tag will be `latest`, the other tag will be a timestamp that follows a YEAR.MONTH.DAY.HOUR.MINUTE format and looks like `2019.04.08.02.33`. 

NOTE: We use Docker [labels](https://support.coreos.com/hc/en-us/articles/115001384693-Tag-Expiration) to remove these images from Quay after four weeks. If you plan to move our hardened images to other Quay repos and not have them expire after four weeks, you will want to remove this Quay-specific label - you can read more about the behavior and remediation [here](https://wwwin-github.cisco.com/sto-ccc/cloud9-docs/blob/master/docs/containers/hardened_containers.md).
